This paper discusses information sharing among organizations for improving cybersecurity, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a game-theoretic approach to understanding firms' incentives in these agreements, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of private and public assessments in designing inter-temporal incentives, which falls under the categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes the use of a public rating/assessment system, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
